# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Line endings — keep Linux scripts LF on EVERY platform, including Windows.
#
#  Why this file exists (do not remove):
#  These shell scripts run directly on Linux / WSL / SteamOS, and are often
#  shared as raw files (e.g. posted to Discord) and run straight from the
#  download. Git's core.autocrlf=true converts text to CRLF on a Windows
#  checkout, which turns the shebang into `#!/bin/bash<CR>`. Linux then fails
#  to run the script with:
#        cannot execute: required file not found
#  because it looks for an interpreter literally named "/bin/bash\r".
#
#  `eol=lf` forces LF in the working tree regardless of OS or autocrlf, so
#  editing the source on Windows can never reintroduce CRLF into a script.
#  (Future extensionless scripts — e.g. a launcher with no .sh — must be
#  added here explicitly by path, since these globs match by extension.)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.sh    text eol=lf
*.bash  text eol=lf
*.zsh   text eol=lf
*.ksh   text eol=lf
*.fish  text eol=lf
